{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b7c23d41-8e55-4f03-9d14-2e6a0b7f1c38",
    "name": "ETH-Liq-LTV-Coll1-1hour-minutely",
    "description": "ACTUS DeFi ETH 1-hour loan: COMPETING BEHAVIORAL RISKS simulation — MINUTELY granularity.\n\nTWO behavioral models run simultaneously:\n  1. TwoDimensionalPrepaymentModel — voluntary rate-driven deleveraging\n     (spread × age surface, checked every 10 minutes = 6 check points over 1 hour)\n  2. CollateralLTVModel — protocol-enforced LTV-driven liquidation\n     (minutely monitoring = 60 check times over 1 hour)\n\nScenario: Intraday ETH flash-crash pattern\n  ETH: $2,280 → $2,210 (~3.1% decline over 1 hour, with minute-level noise)\n     Based on historical ETH intraday flash-crash micro-volatility pattern\n  Rate: 6.75% → 6.85% (gradual minutely rise)\n     Derived from end-of-period values of the 1-week hourly simulation\n  Collateral: 3.0 ETH, initial LTV = 73.1%  ($5000 / (3 × $2,280))\n\nMINUTELY design:\n  Index data: 61 minutely points each (T09:00 → T10:00)\n  LTV monitoring: 60 times (every minute T09:01 → T10:00)\n  Prepayment checks: 6 (every 10 minutes: T09:10, T09:20, T09:30, T09:40, T09:50, T10:00)\n  Rate resets: every minute (cycle PT1ML1)\n\nKey LTV thresholds (Aave V3 calibrated):\n  ltvThreshold  = 75%  → partial repay to target 65%\n  liquidation   = 82.5% → full liquidation\n  LTV hits 75%   when ETH ≈ $2,222  (notional = $5,000, collateral = 3 ETH)\n  LTV hits 82.5% when ETH ≈ $2,020\n  Starting LTV = 73.1% — just 1.9% below threshold, breach expected within ~10 min\n\nScholarly Basis:\n  - Deng, Quigley & Van Order (2000), Econometrica: Competing risks framework\n  - Schwartz & Torous (1989, 1993): Rate-driven prepayment modeling\n  - Qin et al. (2021): DeFi liquidation mechanisms & thresholds\n  - Heimbach & Huang (2024), BIS WP 1171: DeFi leverage & voluntary buffers\n  - Lehar & Parlour (2022), BIS WP 1062: Systemic fragility, cascades\n  - Sadeghi (2025): Liquidation dynamics & transaction fees\n  - Aspris & Svec (2025): Skilled vs unskilled DeFi risk management\n\nOpen Postman Console (Ctrl+Alt+C) before running.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
